Kurt Rambis was fired today as coach
of the Minnesota Timberwolves after losing 100 more games than
he won in two seasons with the National Basketball Association
team.  Rambis, a former championship winner as a player and
assistant coach with the  Los Angeles Lakers , went 32-132 with
the T-Wolves. The team announced his dismissal in a news
release.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  